issue.body:
0b47d7685bc33f80d3ab3ca3339630880d5d1ff0 almost fixed the issue described in #20834.

There's still a problem in the corner case where the parent is `Text` (not `Text2d`) and uses an empty string. Then the first child will use the color of the parent instead of its own.  The other children use their own color as expected.

Code sample to reproduce:

```rust
use bevy::prelude::*;

fn main() {
    let mut app = App::new();
    app.add_plugins(DefaultPlugins)
        .add_systems(Startup, spawn_text)
        .run();
}

fn spawn_text(mut commands: Commands) {
    commands.spawn(Camera2d);

    commands.spawn((
        Text::default(),
        children![
            (TextSpan::new("red"), TextColor(Srgba::RED.into())),
            (TextSpan::new("green"), TextColor(Srgba::GREEN.into())),
            (TextSpan::new("blue"), TextColor(Srgba::BLUE.into()))
        ],
    ));
}
```
